<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">An easy spot for a couple more levels (up to about 44) is Jaggedpine.  Go to the Brell gnoll caves by the Black Burrow portal.  Charm an anchorite; they hit for around 100, but don't dual wield.  Take him to the basilisk caves, and clear them out.  Don't kill your pet, as you don't want the faction hit.
<br />

<br />
Only the genitors aggro, and they also stun.  On a break you can stand and stun or mez and recharm; or you can run for the portal if you don't want to risk the genitors stun proc.  This is an easy spot for learning how to charm.
<br />

<br />
Another spot is Echo Caverns, the Deep side.  Charm the Haven guard at the entrance, and kill underbulks and fungal fiends.  Again, don't kill this pet to avoid faction hits.  In theory you could charm the Taskmaster for faster kills, but his level makes him extremely resistant until you have gained a few.
<br />

<br />
An old popular spot is to charm one of the Kael guards in Eastern Wastes, kill the other guard, and then try to clear the ulthork man-o-wars.  Remember that giants aren't mezzable or stunnable, so distance and root are your only tools.
<br />

<br />
Finally, Dawnshroud.  Charm one of the fireside NPCs (it doesn't really matter much which one), and kill rockhoppers, higher level tribals and stone things.  This is the tougher test of charming.  Splitting your pet is the hard part, closely followed by staying alive on charm breaks.
<br />

<br />
All of that (plus DL) will get you to 53 safely, in time for Nightmare.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
